  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "The BASE_REWARD_QUOTIENT parameter dictates the per-epoch reward. It corresponds to ~2.54% annual interest assuming 10 million participating ETH in every epoch.\r\n\r\nIs there a source for how this figure was computed? (I can get something close, ca. 2.1%, but not this exact figure)\r\nI also would suggest that the maximum reward computation should become part of the spec. Then we could write a test case for it and if rewards are modified to not match this formula we would notice, which I would see as an advantage. Small changes could make a big difference here.",
