    "body": "> I haven't re-run the numbers, but I imagine the 2.54% is compounding whereas the 2.1% is not.\r\n\r\nCompounding make a tiny difference of 0.03% here, so it's not that. I guess I am unsure how many times exactly the base_reward can be applied, the block proposer reward is not obvious. Also relates to #944 -- is the number 5 exact there? Because I feel it's not.\r\n\r\n> Do you mean a formula showing how this is derived?\r\nI would even go as far as including a function that computes the expected rewards per time period. Then we could add a test case and be sure that rewards will be what we expect them to be, no matter how we change the spec later :)",
